<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph id="CF2018_4.27" base="F72786708"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>4.27</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value=""/><data name="paranum" value="4.27"/></prolog><body><p id="CF2018_P0201">For a liability to exist, three criteria must all be satisfied:</p><ol outputclass="static" id="CF2018_L0022" base="F72786710" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="CF2018_P0202" base="SL72787058">the entity has an obligation (see paragraphs 4.28&#x2013;4.35);</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="CF2018_P0203" base="SL72787059">the obligation is to transfer an economic resource (see paragraphs&#xa0;4.36&#x2013;4.41); and</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p id="CF2018_P0204" base="SL72787060">the obligation is a present obligation that exists as a result of past events (see paragraphs&#xa0;4.42&#x2013;4.47).</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>